ss plug)...<br><br>Concentrate on the &quot;pet owners&quot;, &quot;miscellaneous tips&quot;, and &quot;druids and shaman&quot; portion.<br><br>A few things tho since I see yer level 47.  Conflagration us yer nuke of choice.  <br><br>Here's how I would open the fight:<br><br>Golem wand pet, root pet.<br>Golem wand x4 Shaman<br>Conflag shaman till dead, mixing in Shock of Lightning to interrupt healing.<br><br>he's going to try and heal occasionally.  Use your Shock of Lightning (lvl 12 spell) to interrupt heals.  SoL is kewl up till u hit lvl 51ish then after that its just pointless.  Too easy to channel/better spells available.<br><br>So yer fight is going to look something like &quot;conflag shaman, SoL shaman, Conflag shaman, conflag shaman.&quot;<br><br>If you want to spend the money on cure potions they'll run about 250pp I think for 1 10 shot of disease AND poison.<br><br>Stinging wort (300 point heals) cost around 600pp for a 10 charge - but well worth it becuz it is INSTANT CAST TIME.<br><br>Depends on how die hard u are about it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>My guild makes fun of me all the time cuz I'm broke from buying cure potions etc almsot every day....BUT I rarely die, and when I do its usually becuz it was 10 vs 1 or something.<br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>Ace<br>KotWR <p>"Those that can, do.  Those that cannot, summon pets."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uchifiir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chifiir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/27/02 1:12:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a shaman</span><hr size=1> Shaman will melee you, to interrupt.<br>SoW spells/boots  &gt; jboots<br>Even if you dispell his DoTs, they still hurt and force you to strip yourself.<br><br>Pet will be all over you, and if you wand it, then root it, the shaman will unroot it or use the few seconds to start stacking DoTs on you/melee you.<br><br>At 47 with conflag, you're going to have a rough time.  Conflag just takes too long to cast.  <br><br>-Szii <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ullyapakadeabn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llyap aka Deabn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/27/02 3:11:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling a shaman</span><hr size=1> You don't dispel shaman dots, you need cure potions like ace said. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uchifiir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chifiir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/27/02 6:03:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> sigh</span><hr size=1> Of course you use Cure Potions.  <br><br>Either way, it's a dispell.  It's a generic term.<br><br>-Szii Uln'hyrr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usoupypoopy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>soupypoopy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/28/02 1:33:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.doodie.com/pics/slaphappy2.gif.05232001 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sigh</span><hr size=1> I'd say that you need your DR over 80 or 90, your PR a bit higher (because of his Poison-based nukes) and your CR over 150, especially if he has a JBB (the JBB is mana-free cold nukes). You also don't mention if he's got his epic yet -- that's a nice 1000-ish splurt-style dmg dot (MR-based, so you'll have to dispell it like you would WD or Splurt).<br><br>If he goes defensive at first (which I would, if I were facing off against a wizzie) he'll just time heals between your nukes and run you OOM. Then he'll use his mana-free damage (pet, jbb, epic) to kill you. <br><br>So you had better hope that:<br><br>1) you have the resists in place<br>2) he doesn't go defensive<br>3) you burn the hell out of him right off the bat<br><br> <p>--Soupypoopy | Vova Elay <b><a href="http://www.notacult.com">Flower of Happiness</a></b> and member of <b><a href="http://www.tusrz.com">The Usual Suspects of Rallos Zek</a></b><br><img src="http://www.wlau.com/finger.gif"><i>Bringing the Miracle of Teledildonics to the Unhappy Bluebies of Rallos Zek!</i><img src="http://www.wlau.com/finger.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showPrevMessage?top